HEADWORD: Lophophore
<hw>Loph"o*phore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>lo`fos</grk> a crest or tuft + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A disk which surrounds the mouth and bears the
tentacles of the Bryozoa. See <er>Phylactolemata</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lophopoda</ent>⟦br⟧
